HEADWORD: Steppe
<hw>Steppe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From Russ.
<ets>stepe</ets>, through G. or F. <ets>steppe</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of
the vast plains in Southeastern Europe and in Asia, generally elevated,
and free from wood, analogous to many of the prairies in Western North
America. See <er>Savanna</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Steppe murrain</b></col>. <fld>(Far.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Rinderpest</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stepped</ent>⟦br⟧
